President Muhammadu Buhari will be addressing Nigerians on Monday (today) evening ay 7pm. The Senior special Assistant to the President on Media and Publicity, Mr. Garba Shehu, announced this in a series of tweets on Monday. He said, “President @MBuhari will broadcast to the nation Monday, April 13, 2020 at 7pm” “Television, radio and other electronic media outlets are enjoined to hook up to the network services of the Nigerian Television Authority (NTA) and Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria (FRCN) respectively for the broadcast. This will be the second time President Buhari would be addressing Nigerians since the COVID-19 Pandemic got to the country. He did the first address two weeks ago, when he ordered the lockdown of Lagos, FCT and Ogun states in a bid to curtail the spread of COVID-19 in the country.